subject: lung health
content: dear current situation has kept indoors with little physical activity essential that take care ourselves during such times these tough times pranayama can natural and easy way help keep our body healthycovid respiratory disease which affects the lungs since affects the respiratory tract should take efforts increase the lung capacity lung health essential fight corona virus the lungs cannot expand fully leads shallow breathing and decreased lung capacity therefore important keep the lungs healthy with proper breathing effective method increase lung capacity simple and works wonders there are many benefits practising pranayama regularlyit boosts the immune system and helps clearing the nasal passagesit also helpful relieving stress and calming the mindin addition maintaining hygiene practising social distancing washing hands and wearing mask having healthy lungs helps survive the pandemic bettertips for getting exercise should performed clean and hygienic morning the ideal time perform breathing should done with great care and awarenesswe should try stay focused the journey not the should not practised when the lungs are congested the breath should kept rhythmic and steady and eyes should remain closed throughout continue taking deep smooth breaths without any forceif experience any discomfort should stop the breathing exercise immediately and have return normal breathingthose with chronic medical conditions should consult their physician before starting pranayamaheres simple pranayama for you begin with breathing practice abdominal breathing for lower lungsb sit any comfortable position prefer sitting any meditative posesb keep your spine erectb close your eyes that you can focus the breathingb place the hands resting the thighs adi mudra press your thumb the inside the palm the fingers are closed around the thumb both the handb inhale deeply slowly and continuously through both the nostrils the abdomen bulges outb exhale through both the nostrils draw the abdomen inwards slowlyb repeat this breathing cycle five times thoracic breathing for middle lungsb sit any comfortable position prefer sitting any meditative posesb keep your spine erectb close your eyes that you can focus the breathingb place the hands resting the thighs chinmaya mudra join the tip your thumb with the tip index finger curl the rest three fingers the palmb inhale deeply through both the nostrils expand the chest forwardb exhale through both the nostrils relax the chestb repeat this breathing cycle five times upper lobar breathing for upper lungsb sit any comfortable position prefer sitting any meditative posesb keep your spine erectb close your eyes that you can focus the breathingb place the hands resting the thighs chin mudra touching your index fingertip the tip your thumb while holding your other three fingers straightb inhale deeply through both the nostrils raise the shoulder upwardsb exhale through both the nostrils drop down the shoulder the resting positionb repeat this breathing cycle five times nadi suddhi pranayamab sit any comfortable position prefer sitting any meditative posesb keep your spine erectb close your eyes that you can focus the breathingb place the left hand resting the thighs chin mudra and right hand nasika mudra fold index and middle fingers and keep the ring and little fingers straight along with the thumbb place the ring and small fingers the left nostril and place the right thumb the right nostrilb open the left nostril breathe from the left nostril close the left nostril with the small and ring fingers and release the thumb from the right nostril exhale through the right nostrilb next inhale through the right nostril the end inhalation close the right nostril open the left nostril and exhale through itb this completes one round the nadi suddhi pranayamab repeat this breathing cycle five times let stay safe and remain healthy during such difficult times with kind regardsdr subject: guest lecture invitation engineer problem and challenge the space shuttle grind operation team reg
content: dear sirmadamall are cordially invitedschool mechanical engineering smeccordially invites you for theguest problems and challenges thespace shuttle ground operations teambydr ravi margasahayam mbasolar system ambassador nasa jplvip tour guide international public speaker nasa teams pmmeeting link space shuttle totally reusable spacecraft developed nasa starting has been called cathedral technology the glory days the space shuttle era started with the first launch april culminating july over those glorious decades space shuttle was the workhorse space exploration both for the usa and the world nasa had embarked manned space exploration using the space shuttle vehicle the mainstay nasa faced many problems and challenges during the launches that encompassed the year supreme reign the heavens the space shuttle this lecture the technology challenges are presented from the perspective ground systems engineering and operations the nasa ksc and not the flight operations that controlled nasa houston space centerabout the speaker ravi margasahayam currently serves foreign national tour guide and global space ambassador for john kennedy space center florida was nominated astronauts and held the position solar system ambassador for nasa jet propulsion laboratory pasadena california officially retired from nasa after stellar career covering over years was the only person indian origin work both launch pads complex from where nasa sent humans land the moon ravi started his nasa career vibroacoustics researcher followed chief launch pad systems engineer and systems safety engineer the space shuttle program later his career held the highest safety and mission assurance position nasa the cochair ground review safety panel gsrp for all payloads going the international space station hoddda dean smecdr vasudevandr

content: for freshers and introduction python was developed guido van rossum and was released first february one the most widelyused and loved programming languages and interpreted nature thereby providing flexibility incorporating dynamic semantics also free and opensource language with very simple and clean syntax what python python highlevel interpreted generalpurpose programming language being generalpurpose language can used build almost any type application with the right toolslibraries additionally python supports objects modules threads and automatic memory management which help modeling realworld problems and building applications solve these problems what are the benefits using python python generalpurpose programming language that has simple easytolearn syntax that emphasizes readability and therefore reduces the cost program maintenance moreover the language capable scripting completely opensource and supports thirdparty packages encouraging modularity and code reuse its highlevel data structures combined with dynamic typing and dynamic binding attract huge community developers for rapid application development and deployment what interpreted language interpreted language executes its statements line line languages such python javascript php and ruby are prime examples interpreted languages programs written interpreted language runs directly from the source code with intermediary compilation step tonbspread the remaing questions python interview questions click the button below nbsp read nbsp how memory managed python memory management python handled the python memory manager the memory allocated the manager form private heap space dedicated python all python objects are stored this heap and being private inaccessible the programmer though python does provide some core api functions work upon the private heap space additionally python has inbuilt garbage collection recycle the unused memory for the private heap space what lambda python why used lambda anonymous function python that can accept any number arguments but can only have single expression generally used situations requiring anonymous function for short time period lambda functions can used either the two ways assigning lambda functions variable mul lambda printmul output dgt wrapping lambda functions inside another function def mywrappern return lambda mulfive mywrapper printmulfive output dgt how you copy object python python the assignment statement operator does not copy objects instead creates binding between the existing object and the target variable name create copies object python need use the copy module moreover there are two ways creating copies for the given object using the copy module shallow copy bitwise copy object the copied object created has exact copy the values the original object either the values reference other objects just the reference addresses for the same are copied deep copy copies all values recursively from source target object even duplicates the objects referenced the source object from copy import copy deepcopy list shallow copy list copylist list listappend list output dgt list output dgt deep copy list counsel service vit simplify your digital life and mental health quiz reg
content: dear your digital lifefaster than anyone really expected have become fully immersed digital lifestyle theres lot good thats come from the explosion technology and digital communication has definitely made our lives easier faster and more productive but there diminishing point return with our devotion digital devices weve become obsessed with technology and its impacting every aspect how live our lives are slaves the gadgets that were supposed simplify our lives and prefer the quick fix instant information and lowquality entertainment over realworld interactions and experienceswe spend hours social media our inboxes are flooded our desktops are littered our laptops are bursting the seams with more documents photos and downloads than can absorb lifetime digital stuff has insidious way occupying your time with nonessential activities and just like physical clutter your home digital clutter creates feelings anxiety agitation and simple habit eliminate technology overloadif you add the time spent each digital device every day then you probably have closer relationship with the virtual world than you have with your parents family friends you know theres something wrong with this balance and yet you still find yourself flipping open the lid gazing your phone whenever you have moment spare even when you dont this really how you want live your lifewhat your digital mindsetits not news you that your digital devices rather the content them cause you mental distress and agitation none like admit but all know how pervasive the digital world has become our daily livesits you decide how manage the digital intrusion your life and the impact your mental health its important proactive your values and choices related your digital life developing digital value system you create personal boundaries that help you manage your time and clutter both mental and digitalhere are some questions ask yourself that can used create digital boundaries how much time each day absolutely necessary for spend devices for job job that requires spend more time than want behind computer how much time want spend home computer doing work how much time want spend social media for entertainment how much time want spend smartphone for entertainment what reallife friendships have neglected and how want nurture them what family relationship agreements should have place about using our smartphones ipads laptops each others presence what traditions family time like dinners together you want make sacred and personal without the presence digital devices when have downtime what are the top five best ways should use how can deal with the urges surf the net engage social media when really dont want how will commit managing digital clutter doesnt get out handuse your answers these questions write down your values and personal commitments related how you spend your time and energy and off your devices you may fall off the wagon from time time but now you have wagon climb back ontothis article suggest you few actions support your mental declutter habitshow are you spending your digital time take realistic look how you spend your time your devices course there are necessary online activities for your personal and professional life but then there are the hours you spend plugged just surfing the net playing games and checking social media spend few minutes reviewing your day and add the nonessential time you spent plugged document your digital activities throughout the day youll surprised how much time you give away virtual experiencesall this digital input creates agitation and has addictive quality that pulls you away from more meaningful pursuits that energize you rather than depleting youwhere and how can you begin cutting backstart with hour day that you hold sacred and free from any digital time shut down your computer and put your phone into drawer what can you instead engaging digital distractions suggest you read book take long walk exercise talk with friend spend quality time with your parents and family something creative like writing drawing learn new skill meditate listen music ride your bicycle finish projectdo something that real inthemoment and positive that you avoid both the depletion digital immersion and the secondary feelings guilt and anxiety that often accompany too much time plugged inif you take minutes day begin chipping away the clutter youll begin feel increasingly lighter and unfettered you feel you are finding difficult help yourself come out from digital addiction please seek help from counselling divisionworld mental health day observed october every year raise awareness mental health issues around the world and mobilize efforts support mental health this year the theme mental subject: scope news letter reg
content: dear colleagues and students greetings hope that all you are fine and safe very much delighted share our schools first newsletter during the academic year this would bring you the recent updates about the achievements made our school faculty and students moreover this provides opportunity share the exciting developments that took place our school during apriljune very much glad and pleasure informing you that our vit ranked among top the world university ranking times higher education the ukalso computer science vit ranked within universities the world the subject ranking furthermore world university subject ranking our computer science has moved from rank addition teaching and learning through online one our faculty members arun kumar has achieved greater recognition top scientist the world also our school subject wise ranking conducted asia pacific brings our vit into greater heights the subjects programming language and data structure fundamentals secured the first rank and the subjects computer science fundamentals and problem solving has secured third rank moreover during this period about journal publications were published the reputed journals our faculty members glad share that jyotismita chaki has been honoured academic editor plos one journalits pleasure sharing you that nitin singh rajput has published book chapter deep learning framework for prediction classification and diagnosis alzheimer disease machine learning and deep learning the efficacy improvement healthcare systems crc taylor francis group also very happy share you that with the help our faculty members have signed twenty international mous with international universities different areas collaboration during apriljune very much delighted share with you that the following faculty members sureshkumar preetha evanjeline rajakumar murugan madiajegan jothi parveen sulthana and anuradha have transformed their research findings into patents and all the patents are published successfully its pleasure sharing you that research scholars who have registered under the guidance our scope school faculty members have been completed their research work and awarded doctoral degree during this periodit gives immense pleasure sharing the following student thejasvni dhir won honourable mention award representing denmark disec simulated soel model united nations mssubarna lamsal have secured ranking bioinformatics contest rishi anand played role crew accessdenied contest rtvik katarya has attended cyber security summer intership program tanmay vyas and prasoon soni are the winner bhilai hack hackathon yash kumar varma have declared silver price winner for build redis hackathon organized redisconf subarna lamsal and likhitha vajja have won the neo codeathon moreover three journal articles were published reputed journals very much delighted and appreciate the efforts made our students ankush chaudhari bce have created social distancing analyser based artificial intelligence software that detect violation social distancing identify people without face masks and trigger alarmmessage authorities case any violationalso abhinav gupta bce have produced printed face shields and distributed the police officers medical staff and sanitation workers delhi also his team deployed website for fundraising and raised upto for printing face shields during the pandemic situation very much grateful our alumni students kushagra mrpalash and abishek who were the founders dyte real time video and audio sdk organization that makes developers lives easier they offer highest salary package lakhs per annum two vit students also our alumni ashwini purohit bce was ranked one the top young entrepreneurs asia congratulate the faculty members and students who participate samsung prism program that offer industry relevant projects cutting edge technologies along with the team mentors samsungi request you disseminate and share this enewsletter your friends collaborators and others your contactthank you for your continued support our institution and its mission are looking forward meeting you soon with the second issue scope youwith regardsdr ramesh babuprofessor and deanschool computer science and institute technology vit vellore vit recognised institution eminence ioe government indiadear colleagues and nbsp nbsp nbsp computer system databases can vast and complex and such databases are developed using fixed design and modeling approaches what dbms dbms stands for database management system dbms system software responsible for the creation retrieval updation and management the database ensures that our data consistent organized and easily accessible serving interface between the database and its endusers application software what rdbms how different from dbms rdbms stands for relational database management system the key difference here compared dbms that rdbms stores data the form collection tables and relations can defined between the common fields these tables most modern database management systems like mysql microsoft sql server oracle ibm and amazon redshift are based rdbms there are still more sql interview questions for you read click the button below continue reading nbspread what sql sql stands for structured query language the standard language for relational database management systems especially useful handling organized data comprised entities variables and relations between different entities the data what the difference between sql and mysql sql standard language for retrieving and manipulating structured databases the contrary mysql relational database management system like sql server oracle ibm that used manage sql databases what are tables and fields table
